WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.966 --> 00:00:12.429
<i>I love you.</i>

2
00:00:36.411 --> 00:00:38.705
- I've never seen that before.
- This isn't yours?

3
00:00:38.789 --> 00:00:40.040
- It is not.
- How'd you get it?

4
00:00:42.918 --> 00:00:45.504
Blame? I don't know.

5
00:00:52.094 --> 00:00:55.681
All right. Nothing else to see here.
Let's get out the street. Out the street.

6
00:01:35.929 --> 00:01:38.640
This is a safe space. Zack.
Just be honest.

7
00:01:40.434 --> 00:01:42.186
What do you remember about that night?

8
00:01:44.605 --> 00:01:45.814
Bits and pieces.

9
00:01:47.441 --> 00:01:49.610
Like scenes from different movies.

10
00:01:52.321 --> 00:01:54.156
You understand why you're here. right?

11
00:01:58.994 --> 00:02:02.497
You helped a trespasser
live in the walls of your house.

12
00:02:03.415 --> 00:02:07.544
And you stabbed your dad
with a pair of garden shears.

13
00:02:16.136 --> 00:02:18.514
Yeah. I don't know
what the fuck happened to me.

14
00:02:18.597 --> 00:02:19.932
This is good.

15
00:02:20.015 --> 00:02:23.644
You dissociated. and now you're confused
because you're coming out of it.

16
00:02:30.067 --> 00:02:32.069
So. when do I go home?

17
00:02:35.614 --> 00:02:37.074
- That might be a while.
- Really?

18
00:02:37.157 --> 00:02:39.409
Because you're making it sound
so fucking simple.

19
00:02:41.620 --> 00:02:42.871
"It's good."

20
00:02:42.955 --> 00:02:44.623
I'm "just coming out of it."

21
00:02:45.666 --> 00:02:48.126
"Hey. be the man you wanna be. Zack.

22
00:02:48.710 --> 00:02:49.711
Be the man you wanna be."

23
00:02:50.796 --> 00:02:51.797
I didn't say that.

24
00:02:51.880 --> 00:02:54.091
I'm supposed to just be honest.

25
00:02:54.758 --> 00:02:57.219
You can just sit there
and say whatever bullshit you want.

26
00:02:57.302 --> 00:02:58.637
How do I get your job?

27
00:03:08.355 --> 00:03:11.900
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

28
00:03:12.484 --> 00:03:13.944
I don't know what's going on.

29
00:03:14.820 --> 00:03:15.946
Don't be sorry.

30
00:03:16.029 --> 00:03:18.824
Hey. this is a... It's a process. okay?

31
00:03:21.451 --> 00:03:24.955
Hey. you will start to
feel like yourself again. Zack.

32
00:03:27.040 --> 00:03:28.375
Yeah. what "self"?

33
00:03:34.590 --> 00:03:36.258
Care to have a drink with me?

34
00:03:38.051 --> 00:03:39.511
You remember I'm sober?

35
00:03:45.309 --> 00:03:50.981
Sixteen years ago this week.
we closed on this house.

36
00:03:51.815 --> 00:03:54.276
- You were seven months pregnant.
- I was eight months pregnant.

37
00:03:54.359 --> 00:03:55.569
You were eight months pregnant.

38
00:03:55.652 --> 00:03:57.237
Yeah. I was so uncomfortable.

39
00:03:57.321 --> 00:03:58.530
It was so hot.

40
00:03:58.614 --> 00:04:01.867
Left Nat with the babysitter.

41
00:04:03.410 --> 00:04:08.999
Sat on these floors.
waiting for the movers to arrive.

42
00:04:09.082 --> 00:04:10.292
Yeah. and they never came.

43
00:04:10.375 --> 00:04:12.586
Well. they came to 812 West Jones Street...

44
00:04:12.669 --> 00:04:14.505
- Yeah.
- ...in Charleston.

45
00:04:14.588 --> 00:04:16.173
I wanted to murder them.

46
00:04:18.550 --> 00:04:21.178
And all we had to drink were
Nat's juice boxes.

47
00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:22.596
hot as hell from the car.

48
00:04:24.681 --> 00:04:28.519
But that apple juice was
the best drink I've ever had.

49
00:05:01.218 --> 00:05:02.219
You want some lunch?

50
00:05:03.136 --> 00:05:04.471
No. I'm going in the pool.

51
00:07:34.454 --> 00:07:36.665
Whoever it is knew you had a second cam.

52
00:07:36.748 --> 00:07:39.793
